Brazilian mobile payment company $STNE making all-time highs on an absolute and relative basis. Risk is well-defined at prior highs. Even Buffett owns this Tech stock. 

h/t @howardlindzon for putting this name on my watchlist - as long as price is above 46 the bias is higher Bullish

"Imagine a world..."

Where $MS breaks out of a 20-year base!? It's hard to, I know... But definitely time to take it seriously. $XLF $KBE

You know what they say, right?

From FAIL-ed moves come FAST-ly moves.

$FSLY is already more than 7x off its March low.

Sorry, couldn't help myself.
Is it time to start thinking what a move like this might mean for the global economy and equity markets around the world..?  $AUDJPY

Buying any and all weakness towards 18.50 w/ risk defined at the same level.. same guys who took public will likely take private and Goldman will collect fees on both ends.. rinse & repeat, welcome to wall st ;) $LAUR

$SMG just posted 40% YoY revenue growth from their #cannabis business - this was also the first quarter that the majority of its revenue came from cannabis (this is due to seasonal trends in their primary business). So they are just as much a pot stock as any and the fact they’re diversified only makes it more attractive IMO. People are sleeping on this company right now. It’s one of my favorite picks for 2020. Technicals and fundamentals both look great.

Real nice cup n' handle formation on this chart right now with the potential to gap to fresh highs on tmo's earnings report.. so much to like here - great LT growth profile which is diversified yet still has plenty exposure to #cannabis industry - analysts avg PT is just about at current price so sentiment is where we want it too.. long $SMG above 112 all day Bullish

Laureate Education $LAUR - they focus on providing access to higher education around the world, particularly Latin America

This one hits home.. almost 10yrs ago my boss was the majority owner when they were private.. I used to close the books and do the investor rollforwards.. now I just want to buy the breakout! 

Keep an eye on it - its a quality company breaking out of a nice base but also bear in mind this move is news driven so check out the PR and make sure you understand whats going on Bullish

Will buyers defend this key level of interest or will $BAC break below the potential support at its prior highs.. momentum is one more down day away from being oversold.. Keep an eye on it b/c whichever way this resolves will be a good indicator for Financials more broadly.. $XLF

I love this type of setup - a healthy retest/throwback to former resistance turned support after a fresh breakout w risk well defined just beneath current price.. great reward/risk and at least if you're wrong, you'll know pretty quickly & can minimize losses. 

Seeing a lot of these same setups out there right now.. anything can happen, but the way I learned it is to always err in the direction of the underlying trend.. which is UP Bullish

The CPA in me hates this b/c the fundamentals are garbage IMO but I've learned that lesson the hard way before... $UBER just broke out of a multi-month base and is now flagging above prior resistance as well as its VWAP anchored from last years IPO.. hard not to like it long above current prices.. classic trend reversal w/ well-defined risk management level ~34 provides a great risk/reward setup Bullish

As well as the 2nd largest and maker of all my favorite games growing up so maybe I'm biased but both look like they're heading higher to me $EA 

Can also play the overall gaming space via ETF $GAMR Bullish
Video game makers with nice moves this week after breaking out of some big bases recently.. here is the largest in the space $ATVI Bullish

This is a classic technical breakout from one of the lowest beta stocks in the market.. $KO doesn't even move this much on earnings rpts. +4.5% in 5-days on absolutely no news, just a nice gap n' go to fresh all-time highs..

Trading price behavior beats trading the news any day.. Bullish

Not something you see too often.. if Gold $GC_F holds its overnight gains thru tmo it will mark the 10th consecutive day price has closed above the upper bollinger band.. past few days' action confirms the structural breakout.. $GLD $GDXJ 

I'm just as bullish as I was when I presented my LT thesis on @RealVision last year.. a lot of the signals I laid out are still just coming to fruition.. this is a fresh breakout and should have plenty of legs.. watch the interview here: youtube.com/watch?v=29r79S3... Bullish

$ETHBTC pressing on all-time lows... 

Trailing 12-month Returns:

$BTCUSD +88%   |   $ETHUSD -35%

Had a feeling we'd need something special for Gold to finally break out of its 6-year consolidation.. didn't think it would take the President threatening to demote the Fed Chair tho..  Gold futures broke to their highest level since 2013 today.. $GC_F $GLD $GDX

Seeing the leaders of the 2016-18 bull run start to lead again would be a major positive for US Equities.. Lg-Cap Tech & Discretionary $XLK & $XLY are back above their key 2018 highs and just closed within a stone's throw of their ATHs from earlier this year.. Both are sloped up & to the right in the leading quadrant of the daily RRG  which is evidence of their recent strength and relative performance vs the broader market..

Now that we're all going to be crypto billionaires again its important to know which coins are outperforming vs those that are lagging.. $ETD is the only major currency still below its Q3 '18 hi & relative to #Bitcoin its been in a steady downtrend since prices topped last January..  Despite price rallying on an absolute basis the $ETDBTC pair continues to trade near its all-time lows, retesting them just last month..  Money is better put to work in stronger coins like $BTC & $LTC until we see a turnaround in this underperformance..
